="the first ambulance service was also born to serve black communities, before that, it was left to cops. And despite cops being untrained non medical personnel, they thought against the implementation of ambulances, because boy howdy did they love being able to underserve communities."

="There is no such thing as a white cowboy.  When whites did this job they were called 'cowhand.' The 'boy' in cowboy was to demean and infantilise Black (and Indigenous) men.  Enslaved Black and Indigenous men were the first and only people to do this work for many years on Turtle Island."
